<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,886,151,212]" box="[151,886,151,177]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,886,151,177]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,886,151,177]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName authority="Machado &amp; Rafael" authorityName="Machado &amp; Rafael" box="[151,722,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Dicromantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucophaea" status="new species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,475,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Dicromantispa leucophaea</emphasis>
Machado &amp; Rafael
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[735,879,151,177]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,886,151,212]" box="[151,308,186,212]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">(Figs. 11–12)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,261,1930]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,284,261,287]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
ventromedial lobe completely sclerotized and curved; pseudopenis shorter than pseudopenal membrane; lateral lobe of gonarcus large; hindwing with basal space between C and Sc brown; pronotum white to light yellow, except brown area between anterior border and maculae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,261,1930]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,385,373,399]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<typeStatus box="[197,311,373,399]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Holotype</typeStatus>
male.
</emphasis>
Vertex brown medially, yellow laterally and in a central “Y” shaped spot (Fig. 11d). Head in frontal view almost completely yellow, except for central longitudinal dark brown stripe beginning between antennae and ending at labrum. Stripe narrow at frons. Labrum and clypeus yellow area slightly darker than other head sclerites (Fig. 11a). Mandibles and palpi dark brown at apex, other mouthparts reddish brown. Antenna with scape yellow ventrally and reddish brown dorsally. Pedicel and first three flagellomeres reddish brown; other flagellomeres dark brown (Fig. 11a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,261,1930]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Pronotum: nearly straight in lateral view, with few setae on proximal and distal regions arising directly from it surface. Length-width-ratio at maculae: 6.1. Between anterior border and maculae brown, remainder white to light yellow, except two dark brown small central stripes, one anterior and other posterior (Fig. 11d). Pteronotum: with three longitudinal dark brown stripes, one central and two lateral, with light brown stripes between them (Fig. 11d). Mesoscutellum dark brown, except for yellow lateral border (Fig. 11d). Metascutellum completely dark. Both scutella with 5–6 pores each one. Pteropleura predominantly yellow, mesopreepisternum, mesepisternum, mesanepisternum and mesokatepisternum with dark brown spots at the anterior border (Fig. 11b).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,261,1930]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Foreleg: coxa yellow, except reddish brown apex. Trochanter, last four tarsomeres and femur posterior surface reddish brown (Fig. 11f). Femur anterior surface reddish brown except middle region dark reddishbrown (Fig. 11e). Tibia and tarsomere I reddish brown, except for yellow tibia base. Mid and hindlegs yellow, except midcoxa light brown (Fig. 11b). Tarsal claws with six teeth.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,261,1930]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Forewing: length: 
<quantity box="[424,536,1045,1071]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="12.5">12.5 mm</quantity>
, 7 costal crossveins and 12 veins extended posteriorly from RP. Hyaline, except 1M, 1Cu, bases of AA and 1AP, radial triangle and space between Sc and RA brown. Cell1AP apex light yellow. Pterostigma reddish-brown. Veins brown, except AP1, AP2 and AA yellow. RA and C light brown basally, yellow medially, and reddish brown apically (Fig. 
<quantity box="[926,973,1157,1183]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.1" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="g" value="11.0">11g</quantity>
). Hindwing: 6 costal crossveins and 13 veins that extend posteriorly from RP, hyaline except for cell 1M, space between Sc and RA and beginning of space between C and Sc brown. Pterostigma reddish-brown. Veins color similar to forewing, except for AP1 brown, RA, C and Sc yellow, with apex reddish-brown (Fig. 
<quantity box="[865,911,1269,1295]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.1" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="g" value="11.0">11g</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,261,1930]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Abdomen yellow scattered by reddish brown spots ventrally and dorsally. Tergites IV and V separated by a large membrane. Pleura dark-brown. Tergites IV–VI with 2 groups of 6–9 pores in two transverse parallel rows anterolaterally; each group with one or two large pores or a scar between them (
<figureCitation box="[1150,1251,1381,1407]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,261,1930]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Terminalia: ectoproct posterior border rounded. Ventromedial lobe completely sclerotized, curved, with wide internal bend (
<figureCitation box="[383,509,1456,1482]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12b, c</figureCitation>
) with 8–9 stout setae; and narrow external bend with 5–6 stout setae (
<figureCitation box="[1322,1422,1456,1482]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12c</figureCitation>
). Sternite IX posterior border rounded in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[804,911,1493,1519]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12d</figureCitation>
). Gonarcus with small median lobe, hardly visible in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[462,597,1530,1556]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[519,566,1530,1556]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.2" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="g" value="12.0">12g</quantity>
, h
</figureCitation>
), and two large lateral lobes, easily seen in posterior and lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[160,289,1568,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[216,263,1568,1594]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.2" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="g" value="12.0">12g</quantity>
, f
</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite with constant width and with apex bent medially in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1245,1348,1568,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12e</figureCitation>
). Basal two-thirds of mediuncus wider in lateral view and apex bifurcate in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1167,1301,1605,1631]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12e, f</figureCitation>
). Gonarcal membrane with medial group of spinules, group wider than long, touching gonocoxite apex (
<figureCitation box="[1314,1421,1642,1668]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12e</figureCitation>
). Pseudopenal membrane slightly shorter than pseudopenis and with small scales on dorsal surface (
<figureCitation box="[1320,1423,1680,1706]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12e</figureCitation>
). Hypomere apex rounded with small granules (
<figureCitation box="[693,818,1717,1743]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12e, f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,261,1930]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,417,1754,1780]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<typeStatus box="[197,315,1754,1780]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Paratype</typeStatus>
female.
</emphasis>
Similar to male except length-width-ratio at maculae: 5.6–6.4; pteronotum central stripe slightly wider than others; scutella completely dark brown or with yellow spots laterally; pterothorax pleurites predominantly brown with yellow spots at border (Fig. 11c); forewing length: 9.6–12.9; scutella with 2–6 pores each one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,261,1930]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1436,1941,2004]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Terminalia: ectoproct larger than gonocoxite (
<figureCitation box="[744,842,1904,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12l</figureCitation>
). Sternite VIII large and easily seen in lateral and ventral view; in ventral view with posterior border larger than anterior (
<figureCitation box="[991,1087,1941,1967]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12j</figureCitation>
). Spermathecal duct with few bends (
<figureCitation box="[235,337,1978,2004]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12k</figureCitation>
), Fertilization canal narrow. Capsule covered by minuscule setae (
<figureCitation box="[1114,1210,1978,2004]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,255,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[243,1305,194,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[212,1375,194,1707]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dicromantispa leucophaea: male: a, abdominal tergites; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, ventromedial lobe, ventral view; d, sternite IX, ventral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; f, genitalia, lateral view; g, gonarcus, posterior view; h, gonarcus, dorsal view; female: i, fertilization canal; j, sternite VIII and posterior border of sternite VII, ventral view; k, spermatheca; l, terminalia, lateral view. Gonarcal median lobe (gml); gonarcal lateral lobe (gll), membrane (mbn). Scale = 0.1 mm, except for a." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 12i</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
